data.name: richTextBox1.Text
data.value:
Welcome aboard, Captain!
Before you embark on this journey, there are a few rules you must learn.
Target: Your goal is to hunt and kill the Wumpus, one of the deadliest alien species known to mankind. This creature lives amongst 30 different planets that are surrounding us and will constantly travel from planet to planet.
How To Kill the Wumpus: The Wumpus is usually asleep. He is awakened when you enter the planet he is on or if you shoot an arrow, and will sometimes travel to another planet. To kill the Wumpus, you must shoot an arrow at the planet it is currently on and you can only shoot from an adjacent planet. If you miss, you must continue to seek the Wumpus. If you hit him, then mission complete! If you wind up on the same planet as the Wumpus, you must answer 3 out of 5 trivia questions correctly to wound the Wumpus, who will then escape 2-4 planets away.
Arrows: You start with 3 arrows. Each arrow can be shot into an adjacent room. You aim by telling the computer which room you want to shoot into. You can purchase 2 more arrows by getting at least 2 out of 3 trivia questions right.
Secrets: You can purchase a secret by getting at least 2 out of 3 trivia questions right. Some secrets are more useful than others. Possible secrets include the room number where a bat lives, where a pit is, if the Wumpus is within 2 planets of you, the planet the Wumpus is currently on, what planet you are currently on, and the answer to a trivia question you have gotten wrong.
Money And Trivia: On every turn that you move through space, you will be given a gold coin and be told a piece of trivia. There are 100 gold coins to collect in total. Every time you attempt to answer a trivia question it will cost you a coin. Whether you get it right or wrong, it costs you one coin and you will never be asked that question again before the end of the game.
Hazards: Beware of hazards! There are two types of hazards: black holes and UFOs. Two planets have black holes in them. If you go there, you are sucked into the black hole. You can get out by getting at least 2 out of 3 trivia questions right. If you get out, you will be placed back where you started the game. Two other planets have UFOs. If you go there, you are abducted by a UFO and you are flown to another planet at random. After the UFO takes you to a planet, it will fly away to another random planet. No room will have more than one hazard. The Wumpus is not considered to be a hazard.
Ways to Lose: You can lose if you run out of arrows before killing the Wumpus, if you do not answer 3 out of 5 trivia questions correctly when you end up in the same planet as the Wumpus, and if you run out of coins.
I wish you luck, Captain! To infinity and beyond!
